The paper focuses on hand gesture recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of natural human-computer interface, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of image entropy and density clustering for feature extraction suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the introduction of new datasets and the evaluation of the proposed approach on existing datasets indicates a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
